  1005→
  1006→## 10. Reconnection & Resilience
  1007→
  1008→### WebSocket Reconnection (sd1 class)
  1009→
  1010→| Constant | Value |
  1011→|----------|-------|
  1012→| Max reconnect attempts | 3 |
  1013→| Base reconnect delay | 1000ms |
  1014→| Max reconnect delay | 30000ms |
  1015→| Backoff formula | `min(1000 * 2^(attempt-1), 30000)` |
  1016→| Ping interval | 10000ms |
  1017→| Circular buffer capacity | 1000 messages |
  1018→
  1019→### Reconnection Flow
  1020→
  1021→1. WebSocket connection drops
  1022→2. CLI attempts reconnect with exponential backoff
  1023→3. Sends `X-Last-Request-Id` header with last sent message UUID
  1024→4. Server should replay messages sent after that UUID
  1025→5. CLI replays buffered outgoing messages from circular buffer
  1026→6. After 3 failed attempts → state = "closed", fires close callback
  1027→
  1028→### Keepalive
  1029→
  1030→- CLI sends `{"type":"keep_alive"}` periodically
  1031→- WebSocket ping/pong every 10 seconds (Node.js only, skipped on Bun)
  1032→- If no pong received before next ping → connection considered dead → triggers reconnect
  1033→
  1034→### Hybrid Transport (kQA) — HTTP POST Resilience
  1035→
  1036→When `CLAUDE_CODE_POST_FOR_SESSION_INGRESS_V2` is set:
  1037→
  1038→| Constant | Value |
  1039→|----------|-------|
  1040→| Max POST retries | 10 |
  1041→| Base POST delay | 500ms |
  1042→| Max POST delay | 8000ms |
  1043→| Backoff formula | `min(500 * 2^(attempt-1), 8000)` |
  1044→
  1045→URL conversion: `wss://host/ws/path` → `https://host/session/path/events`
  1046→
  1047→POST body format:
  1048→```json
  1049→{ "events": [<message>] }
  1050→```
  1051→
